OL,3,CSark Seigneur 'perplexed' after
OL,4,Celectricity boss threatens to cut
OL,5,Csupply
OL,7,FMr Beaumont hopes that Chief Pleas
OL,8,Fwill be able to complete its
OL,9,Fcompulsory purchase of SEL sooner
OL,10,Frather than later, saying that utility
OL,11,Fcompanies should be in the hands of
OL,12,Fthose who are accountable for their
OL,13,Factions, something he argues Mr Witney-
OL,14,FPrice is not.
OL,16,FThe Seigneur says the situation Sark
OL,17,Ffaces with SEL is "a bit bonkers" and
OL,18,Fdescribed Mr Witney-Price as showing
OL,19,Fthe "behaviour of a caged animal".
